Rating: 4
This soup was fantastic for dinner with a simple salad and whole wheat quick bread. This time I sauteed one small sweet onion with two cloves garlic in olive oil on med heat until translucent, added the stock and pumpkin and allowed it to come to a low boil. After that I reduced the temp to strong simmer and added the coconut milk, cumin, and lime zest. I added the lime juice and cilantro 5 minutes before serving. The slow simmer kept more of the flavor. For a double quantity, I doubled everything beside the coconut milk.

