Rating: 4
This became a four fork recipe with some work. Like others, I started with sauteed garlic and, in my case, shallots which is what I had on hand. My cumin had lost its mojo, and we like heat anyway, so I used hot curry paste and also added cayenne. Then I substituted white wine for the water. But after adding other ingredients, it tasted bitter to me, so I stirred in about 1/4 cup of sour cream and BAM! it went from questionable to fabulous. My boyfriend kept saying, "I want this twice a week!"

