Rating: 3
This soup is tasty, but it definitely needs some spicing up. First, I added a heaping TBSP of dried chipotle powder, but it still didn't have much zip. So I squeezed in some Siracha sauce and that took it from good to delicious. The lime and coconut can stand up to a lot of heat. Next time, I'll add another can of beans. But it really couldn't be simpler to make on a weeknight, especially since it's easy to keep all the ingredients in the pantry.

Rating: 3
a great recipe to start with then personalize. Other pumpkin black bean recipes call for more beans than pumpkin so the finished color looks more inviting but I prefer the taste of this equal-parts version. My changes: I have made this with chicken stock and added leftover roasted chicken or turkey. I have made it with coconut milk or not, have substituted curry powder instead of cumin-yummy with a dollop of Fage yoghurt on top and chopped cilantro or green onion tops! I have replaced the coconut milk with 1/4 c sherry and pureed the beans and added 1 canned chipotle pepper with 1 tbsp adobo sauce then finished with either sourcream or mild cheddar cheese and diced white onions. This recipe has Vitamin A, fiber, iron, warm and filling and CHEAP to make. I highly recommend you try it and make it your own. And yeah, I know changing the ingredients doesnt quite make it Caribbean any more but the world is our supermarket now and anyways Caribbean food has many influences.

