Rating: 3
OK..I just returned from the Carribean, and had a FANTASTIC pumpkin coconut soup at Oliver's in Anguilla. I have made this recipe 2x now, and I have it PERFECT!! If you follow these directions to a T, you will have ALMOST exactly the soup I ate there. Double the cumin.Use 1 can of black beans only. Use 2 cups veggie broth. This recipe makes a lot of soup. If you don't want this much, you could use 1 cup of veggie broth, and half the can of pumpkin. I also added pepper while cooking, and pepper when serving. I also garnished with a ring of lime in the center of each bowl. Presentation is everything!! I know that there are a lot of variations to this recipe in the reviews. Feel free to try them all, of course, but to really stay true to the intended flavors of this soup, do this. It is fantastic..

